article.headline: Valparaiso 74, IPFW 68
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. (AP) -- Dan Oppland scored 26 points on 12-of-19 shooting to lead Valparaiso to a 74-68 win over IPFW Wednesday night. The senior was one of three Crusaders (1-0) in double figures. Jarryd Lloyd scored 12, and Mohamed Kone added 15 points and grabbed 11 rebounds. Valparaiso jumped ahead by as much as 17 in the first half before a layup by IPFW's Tyler Best with 1:39 remaining cut the lead to 39-36 at intermission. Valparaiso shot over 46 percent to IPFW's 37 percent in the half. The lead changed several times in the first 13 minutes of the second half with the Mastodons (1-2) leading 57-52 at the 9:57 mark. But Jimmie Miles' layup with 4:12 left put Valparaiso ahead for good. The Mastodons kept it close until Oppland stole the ball with 15 seconds left and hit two free throws to seal the win for the Crusaders. DeWitt Scott again led IPFW with 26 points, including a perfect 8-for-8 from the free-throw line. The sophomore forward scored 24 in IPFW's win against Southeast Missouri State Monday. Brad Pompey scored 11 points and collected 10 rebounds for the Mastodons. IPFW hit 16-of-18 free throws compared with the Crusaders, who were 11-for-17. But Valparaiso outshot the Mastodons from the field, 43 percent to 35 percent. Both teams were cold from the 3-point line. Valparaiso was 3-for-15, while IPFW was 2-for-16.
